## NuGet Packages

```shell
dotnet add package OpenTelemetry.Extensions.Hosting
dotnet add package OpenTelemetry.Instrumentation.AspNetCore
dotnet add package OpenTelemetry.Instrumentation.Http
dotnet add package OpenTelemetry.Exporter.OpenTelemetryProtocol
```

`OpenTelemetry.Exporter.OpenTelemetryProtocol` covers OTLP export for all three signals.

---

## Program.cs

```csharp
using OpenTelemetry.Logs;
using OpenTelemetry.Metrics;
using OpenTelemetry.Resources;
using OpenTelemetry.Trace;

var builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);

// Define a shared resource for all signals
var serviceName = "MyService";
var resourceBuilder = ResourceBuilder.CreateDefault()
    .AddService(serviceName);

// ── Traces ──────────────────────────────────────────────
builder.Services.AddOpenTelemetry()
    .ConfigureResource(r => r.AddService(serviceName))
    .WithTracing(tracing =>
    {
        tracing
            .AddAspNetCoreInstrumentation()
            .AddHttpClientInstrumentation()
            .AddOtlpExporter();          // default: http://localhost:4317 gRPC
    })
    // ── Metrics ─────────────────────────────────────────
    .WithMetrics(metrics =>
    {
        metrics
            .AddAspNetCoreInstrumentation()
            .AddHttpClientInstrumentation()
            .AddRuntimeInstrumentation()
            .AddOtlpExporter();
    });

// ── Logs ────────────────────────────────────────────────
builder.Logging.AddOpenTelemetry(logging =>
{
    logging.SetResourceBuilder(resourceBuilder);
    logging.IncludeFormattedMessage = true;
    logging.IncludeScopes = true;
    logging.AddOtlpExporter();
});

// ... your other services ...

var app = builder.Build();

// ... your middleware/endpoints ...

app.Run();
```

---

### Key points

- **Default endpoint** is `http://localhost:4317` (gRPC). Override with the `OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT` env var or pass options to `AddOtlpExporter(o => o.Endpoint = ...)`.
- `AddRuntimeInstrumentation()` gives you GC, threadpool, and assembly metrics for free (comes from the `OpenTelemetry.Instrumentation.Runtime` package — add it if you want those).
- Logs flow through the standard `ILogger<T>` pipeline; no code changes needed in your controllers/services.
- For HTTP/protobuf instead of gRPC, set `o.Protocol = OtlpExportProtocol.HttpProtobuf` (endpoint becomes port `4318`).
